3	# Convert: Mindfulness
4	
5	Convert the constrained HTML design to a pixel-perfect Flutter widget using the **stitch-flutter** skill.
6	
7	## Inputs
8	- `.stitch/designs/mindfulness/design.html` — HTML design mockup (written in Flutter HTML Glossary vocabulary)
9	- `.stitch/designs/mindfulness/SPEC.md` — Screen specification
10	- `.stitch/system/DESIGN.md` — Design system specification
11	
12	## How It Works
13	
14	The HTML mockup uses the **Flutter HTML Glossary** — a constrained vocabulary where every HTML class and `data-*` attribute maps 1:1 to a Flutter widget. This enables mechanical, pixel-perfect conversion.
15	
16	## Conversion Steps
17	
18	1. **Read HTML** — Parse `.stitch/designs/mindfulness/design.html` and extract:
19	   - `:root` CSS tokens → update `lib/theme/app_theme.dart` if new tokens found
20	   - `.scaffold` element tree → this is the conversion entry point
21	   - `data-*` attributes → Flutter widget parameters
22	   - `data-animate` attributes → `flutter_animate` chains
23	   - `aria-*` attributes → `Semantics` widgets
24	
25	2. **Walk the DOM** — Process each glossary element top-down:
26	   - `.scaffold` → `Scaffold()`
27	   - `.app-bar` → `AppBar()`
28	   - `.column` → `Column()`
29	   - `.row` → `Row()`
30	   - `.card` → `Card()`
31	   - `.ink-well[data-route]` → `InkWell(onTap: () => context.push(route))`
32	   - `.network-image` → `CachedNetworkImage()`
33	   - `.icon[data-name]` → `Icon(Icons.{name})`
34	   - Text classes (`.title-large`, `.body-medium`, etc.) → `Text(..., style: textTheme.X)`
35	   - `data-color` → `colorScheme.X`
36	   - `data-spacing` → `AppTheme.spaceX`
37	   - `data-radius` → `AppTheme.radiusX`
38	
39	3. **Generate Dart** — Write `lib/screens/mindfulness/mindfulness_screen.dart`:
40	   ```dart
41	   import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
42	   import 'package:cached_network_image/cached_network_image.dart';
43	   import 'package:flutter_animate/flutter_animate.dart';
44	   import 'package:folio/theme/app_theme.dart';
45	
46	   class MindfulnessScreen extends StatelessWidget {
47	     const MindfulnessScreen({super.key});
48	
49	     @override
50	     Widget build(BuildContext context) {
51	       final theme = Theme.of(context);
52	       final colorScheme = theme.colorScheme;
53	       final textTheme = theme.textTheme;
54	
55	       return Scaffold(
56	         // ... mechanically converted from glossary elements
57	       );
58	     }
59	   }
60	   ```
61	
62	4. **Update router** — Add route to `lib/router/app_router.dart`:
63	   ```dart
64	   GoRoute(
65	     path: '/mindfulness',
66	     builder: (context, state) => const MindfulnessScreen(),
67	   ),
68	   ```
69	
70	5. **Verify** — Run `dart analyze lib/screens/mindfulness/mindfulness_screen.dart`
71	
72	## Reference Skills
73	
74	- Read **flutter-building-layouts** for constraint rules (constraints down, sizes up), avoiding unbounded constraints in flex boxes, and when to use `Expanded` vs `Flexible` vs `SizedBox`.
75	- Read **flutter-animating-apps** for Hero transition setup, implicit vs explicit animations, and staggered animation patterns.
76	
77	## Quality Gates
78	
79	- **No hardcoded colors** — `Color(0xFF...)` and `Colors.blue` are banned; use `colorScheme.X`
80	- **No hardcoded text styles** — `TextStyle(fontSize: 16)` is banned; use `textTheme.X`
81	- **No hardcoded spacing** — `EdgeInsets.all(16)` is banned; use `AppTheme.spaceMd`
82	- **No Container abuse** — prefer `SizedBox`, `Padding`, `DecoratedBox` when Container is overkill
83	- **Use const** — `const` constructor wherever possible
84	- **Trailing commas** — on every parameter list
85	
86	## Success Criteria
87	
88	- `lib/screens/mindfulness/mindfulness_screen.dart` exists with valid Dart
89	- Uses `Theme.of(context)` for all styling (colors, text, shapes)
90	- No hardcoded colors, text styles, or spacing values
91	- Route added to `app_router.dart`
92	- `dart analyze` passes
